		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Well, back when I had a mono CRT TV, I just plugged it through the RF antenna, so the sound mixing was already done in the console. Sorry for forgetting that when I wrote my 1st post.<br /><br />I also had an RF antenna adapter for PS1 and PS2, that probably mixed the sound channels before modulating the signal, but I remember that in PS2's case most games looked horrible way too dark to be playable in some cases. It was fine with PS1 though.

		

		</td>
