	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />What ends up happening with a Y-adapter-as-mixer, as I understand it, is that the source's left and right channel output drivers end up fighting over the level of the signal put on the wire, and resistance inherent in the system causes the signal's level to meet in the middle.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


